---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="What sudo make vibe means | sudo make vibe"
  description="sudo = ownership. make = deliberate construction. vibe = AI acceleration. Why all three matter."
>
  <main class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">

    <div class="mb-10">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-3" style="color: var(--accent);">/what-sudo-make-vibe-means</h1>
      <p class="text-lg" style="color: var(--text-secondary);">sudo = ownership. make = deliberate construction. vibe = acceleration.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-10" style="color: var(--text-primary);">

      <div>
        <p class="mb-4">This site is built on a simple idea:</p>
        <p
          class="font-mono text-sm p-4 rounded-lg mb-4"
          style="background-color: var(--bg-card); border-left: 4px solid var(--accent); color: var(--text-secondary);"
        >
          The future belongs to builders who can combine AI acceleration with systems discipline. Not one or the other. Both.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- vibe -->
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4" style="color: var(--accent);">The "vibe" part matters</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">AI can help you explore faster, prototype faster, and unblock yourself faster.</p>
        <ul class="space-y-1 ml-4" style="color: var(--text-secondary);">
          <li><span style="color: var(--accent);">→</span> A prompt can become a script</li>
          <li><span style="color: var(--accent);">→</span> A rough concept can become a working service</li>
          <li><span style="color: var(--accent);">→</span> An architecture idea can become a first-pass configuration in minutes instead of hours</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- sudo -->
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4" style="color: var(--accent);">But the "sudo" part matters just as much</h2>
        <div
          class="p-4 rounded-lg font-mono text-sm mb-4"
          style="background-color: var(--bg-card); border: 1px solid var(--border);"
        >
          <span style="color: var(--accent);">$ sudo</span>
          <span style="color: var(--text-secondary);"> — superuser do</span>
        </div>
        <p class="mb-4"><code class="font-mono text-sm px-1 rounded" style="background-color: var(--bg-card); color: var(--accent);">sudo</code> means ownership. Responsibility. Root-level thinking.</p>
        <p style="color: var(--text-secondary);">It means understanding the machine, not just consuming abstractions.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- make -->
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4" style="color: var(--accent);">And the "make" part</h2>
        <div
          class="p-4 rounded-lg font-mono text-sm mb-4"
          style="background-color: var(--bg-card); border: 1px solid var(--border);"
        >
          <span style="color: var(--accent);">$ make</span>
          <span style="color: var(--text-secondary);"> — build from source</span>
        </div>
        <p class="mb-4"><code class="font-mono text-sm px-1 rounded" style="background-color: var(--bg-card); color: var(--accent);">make</code> means deliberate construction. Repeatability. Systems that can be rebuilt, not just demos that happened to work once.</p>
        <p
          class="font-mono text-sm p-4 rounded-lg"
          style="background-color: var(--bg-card); border-left: 4px solid var(--accent); color: var(--text-secondary);"
        >
          That is the difference between experimenting and engineering.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- What this site is not -->
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4" style="color: var(--accent);">What this site is not</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-1 ml-4" style="color: var(--text-secondary);">
          <li><span style="color: var(--accent);">→</span> not about AI hype</li>
          <li><span style="color: var(--accent);">→</span> not about pretending generated output is good enough by default</li>
          <li><span style="color: var(--accent);">→</span> not about copying commands without understanding what they do</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- The workflow -->
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4" style="color: var(--accent);">The workflow</h2>
        <div
          class="p-4 rounded-lg font-mono text-sm mb-4"
          style="background-color: var(--bg-card); border: 1px solid var(--border);"
        >
          <span style="color: var(--accent);">prompt</span>
          <span style="color: var(--text-secondary);"> → </span>
          <span style="color: var(--accent);">script</span>
          <span style="color: var(--text-secondary);"> → </span>
          <span style="color: var(--accent);">container</span>
          <span style="color: var(--text-secondary);"> → </span>
          <span style="color: var(--accent);">cluster</span>
          <span style="color: var(--text-secondary);"> → </span>
          <span style="color: var(--accent);">system</span>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-secondary);">It is about a better workflow — one where AI gets you to the starting line faster, and engineering discipline gets you to the finish.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- CTA -->
      <div
        class="p-6 rounded-lg"
        style="background-color: var(--bg-card); border: 1px solid var(--accent);"
      >
        <p class="mb-4 font-semibold" style="color: var(--accent);">Ready to go deeper?</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2">
          <li>
            <a href="/manifesto" class="text-sm font-mono" style="color: var(--accent);">→ Read the full manifesto</a>
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="/start-here" class="text-sm font-mono" style="color: var(--accent);">→ Back to start here</a>
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="/projects" class="text-sm font-mono" style="color: var(--accent);">→ See the builds</a>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- Navigation -->
      <div class="flex justify-between pt-4" style="border-top: 1px solid var(--border);">
        <a href="/manifesto" class="text-sm font-mono" style="color: var(--text-secondary);">← manifesto</a>
        <a href="/blog" class="text-sm font-mono" style="color: var(--accent);">blog →</a>
      </div>

    </div>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
